{"parse":{"title":"Harpsichord Viola","pageid":25434957,"revid":850755443,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg/220px-Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg/330px-Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg/440px-Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"400\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Leonardo3-EdoardoZanon-LeonardoDaVinci-Claviviola-Clavi-Viola-Organista-strumentiMusicali-concerto-concert.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Harpsichord-Viola played in New York City in 2009. The working model is on display at the Leonardo3 Museum in Milan, Italy, since 2013</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif/lossless-page1-220px-Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"332\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif/lossless-page1-330px-Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif/lossless-page1-440px-Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1851\" data-file-height=\"2794\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ca_Hoepli_0093r.tif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Folio 93r of the Codex Atlanticus with the designs of the Harpsichord Viola by Leonardo da Vinci</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Harpsichord-viola</b> (in Italian <a href=\"https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clavi-viola\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"it:Clavi-viola\">Clavi-Viola</a>) is an hybrid musical instrument <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>based on the designs of <a href=\"/wiki/Leonardo_da_Vinci\" title=\"Leonardo da Vinci\">Leonardo da Vinci</a> on folio 93r of the <a href=\"/wiki/Codex_Atlanticus\" title=\"Codex Atlanticus\">Codex Atlanticus</a>. It's a different project from the <a href=\"/wiki/Viola_organista\" title=\"Viola organista\">viola organista</a> (folio 886 of the Codex Atlanticus). It is about the size of a child's toy piano. It weighs 33 pounds and straps to the musician's chest. It's unlike anything else in the orchestra. It has the strings of a violin but is played with a keyboard, and it's powered by the musician's legs as he walks. It's built with the materials that Leonardo would have had on hand, including wooden pegs and gears run by twine. In the folio of Leonardo, you can see that the instrument has a harness. So it was invented as a way to play a stringed instrument while marching. The leg pumps a wooden motor, which moves a long loop of horsehair through the instrument. When the player presses the keys, the strings move up against the loop. Edoardo Zanon of Leonardo3 has been working on the re-creation on and off for five years. Leonardo might have abandoned the instrument because the wooden motor and gears make a clacking, grinding sound.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The first prototype has been presented in New York City<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> in 2009.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Massimiliano Lisa, president of Leonardo3, clarified that most of he da Vinci's machines, for example the flight machine, they do not work or other machines were just toys to impress people. In this case, Leonardo created from scratch a new musical instrument and what makes it important is that this it really works.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The working model is on display at the <a href=\"https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonardo3_Museum_-_Il_mondo_di_Leonardo\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"it:Leonardo3 Museum - Il mondo di Leonardo\">Leonardo3 Museum in Milan</a>, Italy, since 2013.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Harpsichord_Viola&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.prism-magazine.org/feb10/briefings.cfm\">\"ASEE PRISM - FEBRUARY 2010 - BRIEFINGS\"</a>. <i>www.prism-magazine.org</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2018-07-17</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-200